            </ul>
    <div class=3D"tab-content">
                    <div role=3D"tabpanel" class=3D"tab-pane active" id=3D"=
s-lib-ctab-29111403-0">
                <div id=3D"s-lg-content-67788795" class=3D"  clearfix">
    <ul>
	<li><strong>Excel</strong>: Excel is the most commonly used resource to cr=
eate charts and graphs. Excel allows you to create data visualization throu=
gh charts, data bars, and conditional formatting.&nbsp;
	<ul>
		<li>PivotTables and PivotCharts are a common way to aggregate data values=
 across multiple dimensions. They allow users to see relationships between =
these dimensions.</li>
		<li>Power Map is an add-in for Microsoft Office 365 Power BI subscribers.=
 It allows you to&nbsp;visualize geographic and temporal analytical data on=
 a map.&nbsp;
		<ul>
			<li>Microsoft Resources:
			<ul>
				<li><a href=3D"https://support.office.com/en-us/article/overview-of-piv=
ottables-and-pivotcharts-527c8fa3-02c0-445a-a2db-7794676bce96?ui=3Den-US&am=
p;rs=3Den-US&amp;ad=3DUS" target=3D"_blank">Overview of PivotTables and Piv=
otCharts</a></li>
				<li><a href=3D"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/previous-versions/msp-n=
-p/dn749860(v=3Dpandp.10)" target=3D"_blank">Visualizing Data in Excel</a><=
/li>
				<li><a href=3D"https://support.office.com/en-us/article/Get-started-wit=
h-Power-Map-88A28DF6-8258-40AA-B5CC-577873FB0F4A" target=3D"_blank">Get Sta=
rted with Power Map</a></li>
			</ul>
			</li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
	<li><a href=3D"https://plot.ly/" target=3D"_blank"><strong>Plotly</strong>=
</a>: Plot.ly is&nbsp;is a&nbsp;web-based data analytics and visualization =
tool that lets users create interactive charts, informative graphics, dashb=
oards, and slide decks with your data to share online with their community.=
 It provides online graphing, analytics, and statistics tools as well as sc=
ientific graphing libraries for Python, R, MATLAB, Perl, Julia, Arduino, an=
d REST. Please note that it is free to use, but to host your visualization =
online you will need to sign up for an account. Also, it will only allow yo=
u to save one visualization so if you need to save more than one, you will =
need to create a professional account.&nbsp;
	<ul>
		<li>Plot.ly Resources:
		<ul>
			<li><a href=3D"https://plot.ly/javascript/basic-charts/" target=3D"_blan=
k">Plotly.js Basic Charts</a></li>
			<li><a href=3D"https://plot.ly/api/" target=3D"_blank">Plotly Open Sourc=
e Graphing Libraries&nbsp;</a></li>
		</ul>
		</li>
	</ul>
	</li>
